      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MICHONNE'S KATANA (8) total forgive first-up when taken back from the outside draw to finish a plugging fourth over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Ready for this trip and further and she gets the right run with the blinkers going on. Each way. FORWARDING (1) finally drawn a decent gate and doesn't have to improve much to win this. Well placed with Stiff's claim after warming up late in the heavy going when fifth over 1300m at Dubbo in a Super Maiden. MISS PEONY (9) starting to find a bit of form and gives the impression this trip will suit. Returned good figures from the wide barrier with a narrow second over 1200m at Warren. Sure to be around the money. WIZARD'S STAR (3) improving gelding resuming. Stretched out in trip with a respectable fourth over 2100m at Beaumont (Newcastle) last December. Fitted with the two trials and stays in the mix.",
